  "prompt": "Which is the best institute in India for doing a hands on course in ethical hacking?",
  "response": "Choosing the best institute for ethical hacking in India can depend on several factors such as curriculum quality, hands-on training, certification value, faculty expertise, and placement opportunities. Several institutes are well-regarded for their ethical hacking courses:\n\n1. **Indian School of Ethical Hacking (ISOEH)**: Located in Kolkata, ISOEH provides practical training and hands-on experience in ethical hacking and cybersecurity.\n\n2. **International Institute of Cyber Security (IICS)**: Based in Delhi, IICS offers comprehensive courses in ethical hacking and cybersecurity with a focus on practical skills and real-world applications.\n\n3. **Institute of Information Security (IIS)**: Located in Mumbai, IIS provides extensive hands-on training, live projects, and a variety of courses related to ethical hacking and information security.\n\n4. **Appin Technology Lab**: Many locations across India offer ethical hacking courses that emphasize practical training and exposure to real-world cybersecurity challenges.\n\n5. **Koenig Solutions**: Known for its global reach and high-quality training, Koenig Solutions offers ethical hacking courses in various cities, with strong emphasis on hands-on learning and international certifications.\n\n6. **Simplilearn**: Online platform offering certifications and courses recognized globally, it includes ethical hacking preparation for CEH, all focused on practical insights and real-life applications.\n\nWhen choosing an institute, it's crucial to consider factors like curriculum relevance, instructor qualifications, student reviews, and course accreditation. Visiting the institutes, talking to alumni, and reviewing their online presence can also provide valuable insights into which institute might be the best fit for your needs.",
